You are working on Bizzkit — a B2B and D2C business showcase and networking platform (like Instagram for businesses).

Tech stack:
- Frontend: React, TypeScript, Vite
- Backend/DB: Supabase (PostgreSQL + Auth + Storage)
- Deployment: Vercel
- Supabase project: https://ganberetmowmaidioryu.supabase.co
- DB client: src/lib/db.ts

Key features already built:
- Auth (login/signup/password reset)
- Business profiles with products/services
- Feed with search and filters
- Real-time messaging
- Notifications centre
- Conference booking
- Go Random speed networking
- Trust Score / KYC system

Coding rules:
- Always use TypeScript with proper types, no 'any'
- Use existing Supabase client from src/lib/db.ts, never create a new one
- Keep components modular and reusable
- When fixing bugs, return only the changed file content
- Mobile-first, must work on iOS Safari
